---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const collectionDescription =
  'A poetry collection by Dai Pan spanning Still Life, Bless You, and Their World — written between 2024 and 2025.';
---

<BaseLayout title="Three Worlds" description={collectionDescription}>
  <main class="reading-page">
    <header class="reading-header">
      <h1>Three Worlds</h1>
      <p class="reading-meta">Dai Pan — 2024–2025</p>
    </header>

    <section class="reading-prose">
      <p>
        Written between 2024 and the spring of 2025, this collection emerged from a quiet withdrawal —
        a final year in New York spent largely alone, where communication grew sparse and something
        harder to name grew in its place.
      </p>
      <p>
        Dai Pan was born in Jiangsu, raised in Shanghai, and has since lived across cities that never
        quite became home. What remains is not rootlessness, but a particular way of seeing: from the
        edges, in transit, between.
      </p>
      <p>
        The work is organized into three dimensions — <em>Still Life</em>, <em>Bless You</em>, and
        <em>Their World</em> — porous and overlapping, the way memory actually moves. You are invited
        not to arrive at anything, but simply to pass through.
      </p>
      <div class="reading-copyright-block">
        <p>
          All poems collected in Three Worlds are the original work of Dai Pan (潘岱) and are protected
          under copyright. No part of this collection may be reproduced, distributed, or transmitted in
          any form without the prior written permission of the author. For permissions and inquiries,
          visit daipan.art.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
